      "evidence": [
        "`config.Conf()` returns the full global config object and is used repeatedly in unrelated domains (e.g., startram API functions, websocket handlers, docker loaders, version routines).",
        "Call sites pull broad config then read only a few fields (`EndpointUrl`, `Pubkey`, `WgOn`, `Piers`, `SwapFile`, etc.), indicating missing narrow domain abstractions.",
        "This pattern makes logic implicitly depend on global mutable state instead of explicit parameters or scoped services."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce domain-scoped read interfaces (for example `StartramSettings`, `RuntimeSettings`, `ShipSettings`) and inject those into modules; keep `SysConfig` global only inside a configuration service that materializes typed snapshots.",
