    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "typed_conf_update_is_thin_wrapper",
      "summary": "`UpdateConfTyped` is a pass-through facade over string-key map mutation, so interface safety is mostly cosmetic.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/config/config.go",
        "goseg/handler/system.go",
        "goseg/handler/startram.go",
        "goseg/auth/auth.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`ConfUpdateOption` is defined as `func(map[string]interface{})`, and each `With...` helper writes string keys into a generic map.",
        "`UpdateConfTyped` forwards directly to `UpdateConf(values)` which merges untyped key/value pairs into JSON (`map[string]interface{}`) without compile-time field guarantees.",
        "Many handlers/routines use these helpers assuming type safety, but the underlying contract remains dynamic and key-string based."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Replace map-based mutation with a typed patch struct plus explicit apply logic (or field-specific mutator methods), so keys and types are validated at compile time and centrally enforced.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "config_ambient_context"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "docker_volume_writer_duplication",
      "summary": "Wireguard and Netdata duplicate the same temp-container volume-write orchestration instead of sharing a reusable abstraction.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/docker/wireguard.go",
        "goseg/docker/netdata.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`copyWGFileToVolume` and `copyNDFileToVolume` both: create docker client, resolve image, create temporary container with bind, start it, copy file, stop/remove, then defer another remove.",
        "Both functions embed nearly identical lifecycle/error handling with only container names and paths changed.",
        "The same pattern appears because there is no shared helper for 'write file into named volume via ephemeral container'."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Extract a shared helper in `goseg/docker` that takes image selector, writer container name, source file, target path, and volume name; make both wireguard/netdata wrappers call it.",
