      "summary": "Package-level event channels are used as cross-module mutable globals, creating leaky and weakly-typed coordination contracts.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/docker/docker.go",
        "goseg/startram/startram.go",
        "goseg/handler/system.go",
        "goseg/handler/urbit.go",
        "goseg/importer/importer.go",
        "goseg/rectify/rectify.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`docker` exports multiple global channels (`UTransBus`, `SysTransBus`, `ImportShipTransBus`, etc.) and `startram` exports `EventBus`.",
